Nate Diaz choked out Logan Paul lookalike after Misfits event in New Orleans 😳🫢👀
Don't mess with @natediaz209... 

#TeamDiaz 👊🏻

Nate Diaz was just defending himself, 
he had no purpose to harm the guy. That's a fact. 
Watch the video 🎥

#JusticeForNateDiaz

In the comments on the last video, many people write that Rodney Petersen is not a professional fighter. And the statistics shown in the video are the statistics of his fights in jiu-jitsu tournaments. Maybe it is so. But does this change the meaning, the message of the video? Of course not. Rodney Petersen, from 2013 to 2015, fought in amateur fights (record 0:6:0). Yes, he lost in all of them, but what's the difference? He's a trained guy anyway, and he's a danger no matter what his MMA record is, you know? Rodney Petersen also has a blue belt in Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu. He has 13 victories in Jiu-Jitsu tournaments. Not bad. In addition, now he's actively engaged in boxing and has even won somewhere once. So, this guy is engaged in MMA and it's just a fact, it's already his problem that his career as a fighter didn't take place, this's not about that.

And in general, does it really matter who exactly tried to attack Nate? A strong enough man rushes at you and tries to come into conflict with you, to fight with you. Does it matter at this moment what his MMA record is? Did Nate just have to stand there and let him attack just because Nate is a professional fighter? It's stupid. Nate had already gone back against the wall from this whole fights, but this guy still caught up with him. Nate had to defend himself. But as it turns out, Rodney Petersen is such a shitty fighter that even minimal self-defense sent him to sleep in a couple of seconds.

#FreeNateDiaz

Hahaha Jake Paul's look after he waved his hands in front of Nate's face. He's scared like a child, and Nate just doesn't care 🤣

#PaulDiaz

Media weekend with Nate Diaz 😎🎤🎥
#DiazPaul

📸 by @mbdoodle

12 DAYS 👊🏻🥊 DIAZ ARMY ❤

#DiazPaul: August 5th, Dallas, Texas.
OFFICIAL WEIGHT-IN! 💥 LET'S GO, NATHAN DIAZ!!! 🥊💪🏻 #DIAZARMY ❤

Nate took 2-4 and 7-9 rounds, Jake Paul took only 2, 5, 6 (50/50) and 10. I don't understand why they gave the victory to Jake? It's not fair, but it's business, right? 🤔

Nate looked very confident and fresh in this fight. I loved how the audience cheered for Nate and chanted «Diaz» every round. It was like Nate was in the UFC, but it was a boxing fight with a different audience. But even there, Nate won the love of the audience ❤ Nate Diaz is the people's champion and no one will ever take this title away from him. It's a fact 💯

I was pleased with how Nate accepted the result of the fight. He just DIDN'T CARE ABOUT ANYTHING and I adore him for that attitude 😂👏🏻

Probably, Nate's next fight will take place with Jake Paul already under the rules of MMA, and there Nate will definitely strangle him, although today he almost did it 👀😎🤣

Congratulations to the whole Diaz team on the good fights and victories today! It's Nate Diaz Army, motherf*****s!! ❤❤❤
